      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly heavy to feel that accepting loss is the only honest choice, yet the belief that \"nothing gets better\" is often a protective shield your mind built to stop the pain of moving forward. Decades of psychological research show that while the initial shock is real, the vast majority of people do eventually rebuild a version of themselves that feels authentic again, even after devastating losses. Please keep reaching out, because handing over your story to a trained professional is often the bravest first step into that unknown future.",
      "source": "target",
